OL,3,CRupert Grint ordered to pay further
OL,4,C#1.8m in tax
OL,6,FThe actor had received a #4.5 million
OL,7,Fsum from a company which managed his
OL,8,Fbusiness affairs as "consideration for
OL,9,Frights, records and goodwill" from his
OL,10,Fwork, which he claimed was a "capital
OL,11,Fasset" and therefore the subject of
OL,12,Fcapital gains tax.
OL,14,FBut HMRC argued that the fee should
OL,15,Fhave been classed as income, and
OL,16,Ffollowing the investigation told Mr
OL,17,FGrint he needed to pay an additional
OL,18,F#1,801,060 in tax.
